    <list type="translations">
        <item xml:lang="zh">馬鞭</item>
        <item xml:lang="och">鞭</item>
    </list>
<div type="definition">
<p>STICK which has ROPES OR LEATHER RIBBONS ON THE TOP, USED FOR STRIKING HUMANS OR ANIMALS.</p>
    </div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>1. The current general word for a whip is biān 鞭, but the word also refers specifically to a leather whip. There is some controversy on whether the biān 鞭 was or was not used to drive horses in early times.</p>
<p>2. Cè 策 refers specifically to a bamboo whip which remained current in Han times. The cè 策 has always been used to drive horses, but seems to have gone out of use in late Han times.</p>
<p>3. Chuí 箠 refers to a bamboo whip typically used driving buffalo or sheep along, but the chuí 箠 was also used with horses.</p>
<p>NB: Zhàng 杖 refers to a cane for beating prisoners.</p>
        </div>
<div type="huang-jingui">
<p>HUANG JINGUI 2006</p>
<p>COMM 21.</p>
<p>鞭，先秦作名詞時指皮革做的驅人毆人工具，亦可指驅馬工具；魏晉之後也可泛指策，表明作驅馬工具的通稱，有口語色彩。</p>
<p>策，先秦以來專用以驅馬的工具，由若干竹條併合編連而成；引申可指駕馭馬的工具，包括韁繩之類。</p>
<p>箠，本指荊楚之類，不限於驅馬，亦可用於毆人和驅趕共他家畜，從漢代開始，箠亦可泛指驅馬工具。</p>
<p>[ 竹＋內 ] ，小車所用驅牲口器具，頂端有 “ 箴 ” ，但整個古代均不見用例，似是 “ 箠 ” 的異體字。</p>
        </div>
<div type="modern-chinese-criteria">
<p>鞭子</p>
